The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 November is 5,872 (679.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 October, there were 801 new confirmed cases (92.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 October, there were 532 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 51% ( 269 extra cases).
